data.title: General Notifications
data.text:
Notifications of ONLY last six (6) months are available for display. For older notification, you can search for it through the search button located at the top right corner of this window.

List of 3 (three) persons who have been unanimously elected as members to the Executive Council, G.U. by the Gauhati University Court in its Annual General Meeting held on 31.01.2024

Constitution of a Scrutiny Committee for scrutiny of nomination papers, counting of votes (if needed) etc. for the already notified election of 10 (ten) persons College Teachers and Associate Professors and Assistant Professors representatives as members to G.U. Court

Fixture and Provisional Electoral Roll for the election of 10 (ten) persons of whom at least 2 (two) shall be from the Professional Degree colleges to be elected by the Teachers other than the Heads of the Departments and Professors of the Departments of the University and the Principals of the constituent and Affiliated Degree colleges from amongst themselves to the Gauhati University Court

List of valid nomination papers for the Election of 7 (seven) Representatives of Post-Graduate students and 2 (two) Representatives of Law College students to the Gauhati University Court

Constitution of a Scrutiny committee for scrutiny of nomination papers, counting of votes (if needed) etc. for the Election of 7 (seven) Representatives of Post-Graduate students and 2 (two) Representatives of Law College students to the Gauhati University Court

Election of 7 (seven) Representatives of Post-Graduate students and 2 (two) Representatives of Law College students to the Gauhati University Court

(This supercedes the earlier notification vide No. GU/M/R/EL/Court/2023/9282-9300 dated 11.12.2023)

Election of 10 (ten) persons of whom at least two shall be from professional Degree Colleges to be elected by the Teachers, other than the Heads of Department and Professors of the Departments of University and the Principals of the constituent and Affiliated Degree Colleges from amongst themselves to the Gauhati University Court

All students getting fellowship/scholarship etc. under DBT mode are requested to submit their necessary certificate(s) within last day of same month to the Project Cell, 2nd floor, Administrative Building, G.U.

Online applications are invited from eligible faculty members of Gauhati University from 10.07.2023 to 31.07.2023 at https://iqac.gauhati.ac.in/cas for Screening-cum-Evaluation for upgradation of Academic Levels as per the UGC Regulations, 2018

External Examinations

Department wise List of Candidates as prepared in pursuance of Judgement & Order dated 21/12/2022 in WP(C) No/8289/2022 and Order dated 09/01/2023 in I.A.(C) No. 24/2023 for PWD Candidates for appointment.

Fixture for the ensuing election of one Principal out of two non govt. affiliated colleges of this University as member to the Executive Council of Gauhati University

Final list of candidates contesting for the Election of 7 (seven) Representatives of Post-Graduate students and 2 (two) Representatives of Law College Students to the Gauhati University Court for the session 2022-23

List of valid nomination papers of candidates for Election of 7 (seven) Representatives of Post-Graduate students and 2 (two) Representatives of Law College Students to the Gauhati University Court

Scrutinee Committee for the already notified Election of 7 (seven) Representatives of Post-Graduate students and 2 (two) Representatives of Law College Students to the Gauhati University Court

Procedure to be followed by all Deans of Faculties, Heads of the Departments and Faculty members in order to keep proper record of different types of leave and for faster processing

Election of 5 (five) persons of whom at least one shall be a Principal of a Professional College, elected by the Principals of colleges, from among themselves to the Academic Council of Gauhati University

Notification reg. collection of Convocation Certificates and Robes for those who are yet to collect

National Symposium on "Sanskrit Studies in Assam through the Ages and the Role of Sanskrit Teachers in Implementation of NEP 2020"

Nominated members to the Executive Council, G.U. as per provision under section 12(1) (xvi) of G.U. Act 1947

Invitation to the celebration of the Republic Day of the Country and the 75th Foundation Day of the University

Nomination of Dr. Hiranya Kumar Sarma, Executive Council Member and Principal, Suren Das College, Hajo, as member of the Selection Committee for Appointment, Scale Promotion, Promotions, Permanent absorption, Service Confirmation etc. for group 'B' Officers of Gauhati University

Nomination of Prof. Kishore Kumar Das, Dean of Science Faculty and Head of Statistics deptt., G.U. as member to the "Expert Committee" for on the spot inspection of Arya Vidyapeeth College

Election of 7 representatives of PG and 2 representatives of Law College students to the Gauhati University Court

Class Cancellation notice (on 8th January, 2022 from 10:30 am to 1:30 pm)
